This paper discusses a framework for mitigating spam messages in mobile communication. The topic of spam messages is related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed framework involves the use of content-based filtering and challenge-response, which are techniques that fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the trade-offs between accuracy and communication overhead, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR, followed by cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.DS.
